<h1>Quiz Night II!</h1>
<p>These are the questions that I asked during the second Quiz Night Event held on Thursday 28th March. If you couldn't attend now is your chance to have another go! Read Vulnax's article <a href="article.fod_IssueId_15_ArticleId_1309">here</a> to find out how everyone else did. Send in your answers to me at <a href=mailto:karya@muddled-times.com>karya@muddled-times.com</a> to get your points prizes!</p> 
<h2>Round 1 - GENERAL KNOWLEDGE</h2>
<p>1 point for each correct answer.</p>
<ol>
<li>Which weapon is found in the mausoleum? 
<li>Which big cats live in and around the Blizzard? 
<li>According to the chart, who did the druids worship? 
<li>Specifically, where is the highest point of all The Land? 
<li>What item does the ogre carry? 
<li>What does the golem protect? 
<li>What piece of jewellery does the mermaid carry? 
<li>Where does the obsidian normally start at the beginning of a reset? 
<li>What is written on the streetsign? 
<li>What do the rats protect? 
</ol> 
<h2>Round 2 - LISTS</h2>
<p>From the following lists name the odd one out for 5 points, then give a reason why for a further 3 points.</p>
<ol>
<li>Shrine, hallowed chamber, small temple, meditation room 
<Li>Thief, man, maiden, mermaid 
<li>Pick0, dagger0, mallet, shortsword 
<li>Abstract, nightcap, barometer, tapestry 
<li>Beer, vodka, claret, scrumpy 
<li>Hall, woodsman's hut, entrance to monastery, ground floor of keep 
<li>Inside belfry, inside gazebo, barn, bandstand 
<li>Eating room, relics room, underground room, wine store 
</ol>
<h2>Round 3 - ORIENTATION</h2>
<p>Name the place that the following directions take you to. 5 points for each correct answer.</p>
<ol>
<li>Entrance of Maze.in.north.down.east.northeast.east.north 
<li>Vicious Rocks.southeast.southeast.east.east 
<li>Dwarfen Hall.north.north.east.northeast 
<li>Small Bedroom.out.south.west.southwest 
<li>Ground Floor of Scriptorium.south.northwest 
</ol>
<p>Name the building that the following applies to. 5 points for each correct answer.</p>
<ol>
<li>Which building or structure contains trophies of animals hunted? 
<li>Which building has a concave roof? 
<li>Which building is surrounded by snow? 
<li>Which building contains a barbecue in its grounds? 
<li>Which oriental-style building is entered through gates? 
</ol>
<h2>Round 4 - EXPLORATION</h2>
<p>15 points for each correct answer. You'll probably need to wander around The Land to do this section. The particpants in the event did so.</p>
<ol>
<li>Name the room where you can see the BACK YARD OF INN from the window.
<li>What colour is the bedroom in the Alpine Cottage decorated? 
<Li>What is the bridge at the GLASSY POOL made of? 
<li>The walls of which room are covered in painted designs of rugs, bedlinen and clothing? 
<li>In which room location would you find the following, "... some eerie, granite steps to the southwest lead downwards to the cellar.". 
<li>Name the room where you can see the EAST PASTURE from the window.
<li>Which building can be seen from one of the windows of the BEDROOM in the Inn. 
<li>What is the RUIN a ruin of? 
<li>What is the purpose of the HAHA? 
<li>What crop is grown outside the Dwarfen Citadel? 
</ol>
<h2>Round 5 - MUD HISTORY</h2>
<p>This round has 10 points for each correct answer (for the purposes of this quiz, this SYSTEM includes the time spend at Wireplay).</p>
<ol>
<li>Which notorious PK-er arch-wizard previously ran a non-PK MUD2? 
<li>Who was the first witch on this system? 
<li>In which town was MUD born? 
<li>Which company employed Richard to work on MUD2 and further related games? 
<li>What was the name of the first server at Wireplay? 
<li>What is the name of the current server? 
<li>Who was the first person to post a message on the BB on this system? 
<li>Name the only orginal MUD1 still running. 
<li>Who runs it? 
<li>In which year was MUD written? 
</oL>
<h2>Round 6 - GENERAL KNOWLEDGE PART 2</h2>
<p>10 points for each correct answer and 5 points deducted for each incorrect answer.</p>
<ol>
<li>Which animal is the stuffed head from? 
<li>From which tree is the forest made up of on the Dragon Island? 
<li>How many vases are there in The Land? 
<li>Which mobile is "very large and very angry"? 
<li>What is the effigy made out of? 
<li>Which room has velvet-covered furniture? 
<li>Which mobile is described as velvet-skinned? 
<li>What sort of jam does jamjar2 contain? 
<li>How many snakes are there in The Land? 
<li>What is ring9 (the one found in the Keep) made of? 
<li>What are the shoes made of? 
<li>What food is found in the canteen? 
<li>How many flies are there in The Land 
</ol>
